@prefix : <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@base <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8#> .

<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8> rdf:type owl:Ontology ;
                                                                          :Other_Notes "" ;
                                                                          rdfs:comment """There is often no clear quantitative index for landslide stage prediction, and the common methods are based on the landslide deformation stage curve, using different interpolation, parameters, and models to estimate and predict. Even landslides in most regions need to be modeled in one place, one place and one data, which is because there is a very large variability in landslides, even if they meet the third definition of geography, landslides bred in almost the same environment often have different development states, inducing factors, and damage degrees. The occurrence, intensity, and data of landslides are often varied, and only a preliminary internal cause is a variety of geology, topography, hydrology and other factors, which are superimposed on some very complex factors, and even about the very important external factors for a landslide to really occur in the end, what is the troublesome problem.

In this project, the evolution basis of landslide generality, the disaster-bearing environment, and the interaction between related factors are sorted out in the form of knowledge graph. It can contribute to the study of landslides, the prevention and control of landslides, and even the trial prediction of landslides.

But the reality is often also out of the a priori stage. The actual monitoring and early warning is still inseparable from the physical equipment on the ground. Even what stage of development it is in, and the actual direction of development in which the landslide will continue to evolve in the later stage, depends mainly on the experience of experts. Not only in the field of landslides, but even in all areas of natural disaster prediction, it is a battle against the \"sky\"."""@zh-cn .

