###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Bishop_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Bishop_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Empirical_model> ,
                                                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                        owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength>
                                                                                                      ] ,
                                                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                        owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                      ] ,
                                                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                        owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                      ] ,
                                                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                        owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                      ] ,
                                                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                        owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                      ] ;
                                                                                      <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Bishop model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                       "The Bishop model is an empirical model based on the tangent method to analyze the stability of slopes. The model assumes that the slope surface is a rigid plane, and the shear strength and stability conditions of the soil are considered by the tangent method" ;
                                                                                      <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Force Balance Principle: The Bishop model is based on the force balance principle and considers the force of the landslide body in a steady state. In the model, the main forces on the landslide body include self-weight, support force, and shear strength. By analyzing the balance of these forces, the stability of the landslide body can be assessed.
2. Friction angle and shear strength: The internal friction angle and shear strength of the landslide material are considered in the model, and these parameters reflect the basic characteristics of the shear performance of the soil. Through the reasonable estimation and selection of these parameters, the stability of the soil under different conditions can be evaluated.
3. Hydraulic factors: The influence of hydraulic factors on the stability of landslides is usually also considered in the Bishop model. The influence of moisture on the mechanical properties of soil mass and the influence of water pressure on the stability of the landslide will be taken into account in the model.
4. Sliding surface shape: Reasonable assumptions are usually made about the shape and position of the sliding surface in the model, and the shear stress and shear strength on the sliding surface are calculated based on these assumptions to evaluate the stability of the landslide.
5. Parameter selection and fitting: The use of the Bishop model requires reasonable selection and fitting of relevant parameters, and it is usually necessary to determine the values of these parameters based on field survey data, laboratory test results or other engineering experience.""" .


