###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cam-clay_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cam-clay_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                        rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_modulus>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                        ] ;
                                                                                        <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Cam-Clay model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                         "The Cam-Clay model is a widely used constitutive model of soils, which is mainly used to describe the nonlinear constitutive behavior of cohesive soils, including the compression and shear properties of fine-grained and soft soils." ;
                                                                                        <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Plastic Flow Rules: The Cam-Clay model uses a specific plastic flow rule to describe the compression and expansion behavior of soils. In this model, the soil is treated as a plastic material, and its deformation is controlled by the plastic flow criterion. This plastic flow rule is usually based on the strength and deformation properties of the soil under effective stress.
2. Stress-strain relationship: The Cam-Clay model establishes the relationship between stress and strain, and considers the deformation characteristics of the soil under different stress states. The model usually includes parameters such as the compression index and expansion index of the soil to describe the mechanical response of the soil during loading and unloading.
3. Model parameters: The parameters of the Cam-Clay model include some basic property parameters of the soil, such as the initial compression index, the initial expansion index, the compression modulus, etc. These parameters are usually determined by laboratory tests or site surveys.
4. Pore water pressure effect: The Cam-Clay model also considers the influence of pore water pressure on soil strength and deformation characteristics, so it can better describe the mechanical response of soil when analyzing saturated and unsaturated soils.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Centrifugal_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Centrifugal_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                           rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Physical_model> ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Boundary_parameters>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cohesion>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Slope,_aspect,_elevation>
                                                                                                           ] ;
                                                                                           <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Centrifugal modeling is a method of simulating real-world geological conditions by rotating the model stage at high speed. This model can simulate large-scale landslides or geological hazards and observe the movement of the soil in the model." ;
                                                                                           <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Principle of centrifugal force: The centrifugal mode uses the principle of centrifugal force to simulate the response of the soil under earthquake or other external loads by placing the experimental model on a centrifuge and using the centrifugal acceleration generated by high-speed rotation. Centrifugal force can multiply, fivefold, or even multiply the gravitational field in the model, thereby speeding up the geological processes in the model and greatly reducing the experimental time.
2. Control of scale effects: In centrifugal mode, the proportions of length, time, and force in the model are maintained with appropriate scaling to ensure similarity between the experimental model and the actual situation. This means that the stress, deformation and other effects of soil particles in the model are similar to the actual situation.
3. Selection of model soil: In centrifugal mode, it is necessary to select a suitable model soil to replace the actual soil, usually using fine-grained materials such as powdery matter, sand, etc. The physical properties of the model soil need to be similar to the actual soil, and the material needs to have good compressibility and measurability.
4. Simulation of loading conditions: In centrifugal mode, different earthquakes or other external load conditions, such as applying water pressure, simulating seismic waves, etc., can be simulated by adjusting the speed and loading mode of the centrifuge. This makes it possible to simulate a variety of complex mechanical actions during a real landslide.
5. Data acquisition and analysis: The centrifugal mode is usually equipped with sensors and data acquisition systems for real-time monitoring of changes in soil displacement, stress, strain and other parameters in the model. Through the analysis and interpretation of experimental data, detailed information about the behavior and mechanism of landslides can be obtained.""" .


