###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Coefficient_of_friction
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Coefficient_of_friction> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                 rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/c._Physical_parameters> ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "is a parameter that describes the ability of rock particles or rock surfaces to resist sliding against each other" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cohesion
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cohesion> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                  rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/c._Physical_parameters> ;
                                                                                  <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Cohesion refers to the mutual attraction or binding force between rock and soil particles. In the absence of cohesion, cohesion is the main force that keeps the overall structure of rock and soil stable." ,
                                                                                                                                                                   "Cohesiveness refers to the attraction or adhesion between the surfaces of rock and soil particles. Cohesion is caused by the presence of adsorption of moisture, ions, charge, and other factors on the surface of the particles. Cohesiveness is a factor that affects the intergranular bonding force within rock and soil mass, especially in soils containing clay minerals" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compression_shear_test
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compression_shear_test> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus> ,
                                                                                                                <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength> ;
                                                                                                <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Compressive shear test: Compressive shear test can also be used to determine the tensile strength of rocks. In the test, a rock sample is placed in a compression-shear testing machine and a forward pressure perpendicular to the shear plane is applied while a shear force is applied until the rock sample is damaged. The tensile strength of a rock can be estimated by measuring the maximum shear strength of a rock sample." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                                "Compressive shear test: The compressive shear test is a commonly used experimental method to calculate the shear modulus of a rock by applying axial pressure and a shear force perpendicular to the axial direction on a rock sample, while simultaneously measuring stress and strain." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compression_test
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compression_test> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                          rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cohesion> ,
                                                                                                          <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus> ,
                                                                                                          <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle> ;
                                                                                          <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Compression Test: A compression test can be used to determine the compressive strength and cohesion of rocks or certain special types of soil. In a compression test, a vertical load is applied and the deformation and stress of the material are recorded, and the value of the cohesion force can be calculated." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                          "Compression Test: A compression test is a commonly used experimental method to determine the compressive strength and elastic modulus of soil or rock. In a compression test, a numerical value of the modulus of elasticity can be calculated by applying a vertical load and recording the deformations and stresses of the material." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                          "Compression Test: In a compression test, information on cohesion can be obtained by applying a vertical load and recording the deformation and stress of a soil or rock sample. This method is usually suitable for soils or rocks with some cohesiveness." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                          "Compression Test: Through the compression test, the deformation characteristics and strength parameters of the rock under pressure can be determined. In a triaxial compression test, the pressure in the vertical direction is applied while the shear force in the horizontal direction is measured, and the internal friction angle can be calculated by changing the ratio of the horizontal shear force to the vertical pressure." ;
                                                                                          rdfs:comment "" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_modulus
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_modulus> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/c._Physical_parameters> ;
                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Compressive modulus refers to the elastic deformation properties of a rock under compressive stress. It describes the stress-strain relationship of a rock during compression, in megapascals (MPa)" ;
                                                                                             rdfs:comment "" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                              rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/c._Physical_parameters> ;
                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Compressive strength refers to the maximum stress that a rock can withstand under compressive stress, measured in megapascals (MPa)" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Confined_pressure_osmosis_test
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Confined_pressure_osmosis_test> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                        rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure> ;
                                                                                                        <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Confined pressure permeability test: The relationship between pore water pressure and confining pressure can be obtained by conducting permeability experiments under different confining pressure conditions to observe the change of pore water permeability with confining pressure." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                                        "Groundwater simulation experiment: Simulate the pressure of groundwater on rocks, and obtain the pore water pressure under different groundwater conditions through experiments." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/d._Mechanical_model> ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Coefficient_of_friction>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_modulus>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                            ] ,
                                                                                                            [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                              owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                              owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                            ] ;
                                                                                            <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> """In the field of landslide research, constitutive models can involve models that describe the elasticity, plasticity, creep, and damage of different materials such as soil and rock
Soil or rock mechanical parameters: These parameters describe the mechanical properties of the soil or rock, including elastic modulus, Poisson's ratio, shear strength, etc. These parameters can be obtained from indoor trials, outdoor trials, or data from existing literature and databases.

Pore Water Parameters: Pore water parameters describe the water characteristics in a soil or rock, including saturation, permeability coefficient, pore water pressure, etc. These parameters can be obtained from hydrological observations, hydrological experiments, or data from existing literature and databases.

Friction parameters: Friction parameters describe the internal friction characteristics of a soil or rock, including the internal friction angle, coefficient of friction, etc. These parameters can be obtained from indoor trials, outdoor trials, or data from existing literature and databases.

Seepage parameters: Seepage parameters describe the characteristics of water flow in soil or rock, including permeability, permeability, etc. These parameters can be obtained from hydrological observations, hydrological experiments, or data from existing literature and databases.

Material Density Parameter: A material density parameter describes the density properties of a soil or rock. These parameters can be obtained through field sampling, laboratory trials, or data from existing literature and databases.

Deformation parameters: Deformation parameters describe the strain properties of a soil or rock, including compressive modulus, shear modulus, and so on. These parameters can be obtained from indoor trials, outdoor trials, or data from existing literature and databases.""" .


