                                                                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                                                 ] ;
                                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "A model used to describe the stability of a landslide or slope that takes into account the effect of water flow on the seepage of the soil and the consolidation of the soil. The model couples the seepage equation and the consolidation equation to consider the effects of water flow and consolidation on the stability of the landslide." ;
                                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Pore water pressure and effective stress: In the soil, there is water in the pore space, and the presence of water will have an impact on the mechanical properties of the soil. The seepage-consolidation coupling model considers the influence of pore water pressure on the effective stress of soil, that is, pore water pressure will reduce the effective stress of soil, thereby affecting the strength and deformation characteristics of soil.
2. Seepage equation: The seepage-consolidation coupling model describes the migration law of water in the soil through the seepage equation. This usually includes Darcy's law or a more complex seepage equation that describes the flow of water through the pores of the soil.
3. Consolidation deformation: Consolidation deformation will occur when the soil is subjected to external or hydraulic loads. The consolidation deformation is caused by pore water pressure, soil particle rearrangement and other factors, which affect the volume change and mechanical properties of the soil. The combined seepage-consolidation model considers the influence of water migration on soil consolidation deformation and the influence of soil consolidation deformation on water migration.
4. Coupling relationship: The coupling model describes the interaction between water and soil mass mechanical properties by establishing the relationship between pore water pressure and effective stress, as well as the relationship between water transport and soil deformation. This coupling allows water transport and soil consolidation to interact with each other, resulting in a more accurate description of the mechanical and hydrological responses of the soil.。""" .


