###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Drucker-Prajer_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Drucker-Prajer_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                              rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_modulus>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                              ] ;
                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Drucker-Prager model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                               "Similar to the Mohr-Coulomb model, the Drucker-Prager model is a commonly used plastic constitutive model that introduces flow rules to more accurately describe the nonlinear and plastic deformation of soils." ;
                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Yield criterion: The Drucker-Prager model uses a yield criterion based on normal and shear stress states. In this model, the yield condition of the material is described as a linear criterion, i.e., when the equivalent stress (von Mises stress) of the material reaches a certain yield criterion, the plastic deformation of the material begins.
2. Stress space: Unlike the von Mises model, the Drucker-Prager model uses a specific stress space shape to describe the strength conditions of the material. Specifically, the Drucker-Prager model assumes that the strength condition of the material is presented in the stress space as a cone, the shape of which is determined by the cohesion angle and friction angle.
3. Stress-Strain Relationship: Once the material reaches the yield criterion, the Drucker-Prager model determines the magnitude of the plastic strain based on the strength condition and strain state of the material. In the model, the influence of normal stress and shear stress on the deformation of the material is usually considered, and the stress-strain relationship is established on this basis.
4. Model Parameters: The two key parameters of the Drucker-Prager model are the cohesive and frictional angles, which describe the cohesive properties and frictional properties of the material, respectively. These parameters are usually determined by trial or other means.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Dynamic_compression_test
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Dynamic_compression_test> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                  rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_modulus> ,
                                                                                                                  <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio> ;
                                                                                                  <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Dynamic compression test: Dynamic compression test usually uses techniques such as shock wave or ultrasound to calculate the compressive modulus of a rock by measuring the velocity and strain relationship of a rock sample under dynamic loading." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                                  "Seismic wave velocity determination: Using seismic wave velocity measurement technology, the propagation velocity of seismic waves in the rock can be determined by placing geophones and exciters on the rock mass, so as to reverse the elastic parameters of the rock, including the compressive modulus." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                                  "Seismic wave velocity measurement: The Poisson's ratio of the rock can be calculated by measuring the longitudinal wave velocity and shear wave velocity of the seismic wave in the rock by using the seismic wave velocity measurement technology." .


