###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Fellenius_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Fellenius_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                         rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Empirical_model> ,
                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength>
                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                         ] ;
                                                                                         <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Ferennius model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                          "The Fellenius model is an empirical model for determining the bearing capacity of pile foundations. It takes into account the lateral bearing capacity and the end bearing capacity of the pile, and provides an estimate of the bearing capacity of the pile foundation through an empirical formula." ;
                                                                                         <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Force Balance Principle: The Fellenius model is based on the force balance principle and considers the force of the landslide body in a steady state. In the model, the balance analysis of various forces on the landslide body, including self-weight, support force, shear strength and the influence of hydraulic factors on the landslide.
2. Soil shear strength: The shear strength characteristics of soil materials will be considered in the model, and the shear strength of the landslide body under different conditions will be evaluated by determining the shear strength parameters of the soil. Commonly used shear strength parameters include internal friction angle and cohesion.
3. Hydraulic factors: The Fellenius model also considers the influence of hydraulic factors on the stability of the landslide, including the increase in saturation caused by rainfall and the increase in water pressure. The shear strength of the soil is modified according to the hydraulic conditions in the model to consider the influence of hydraulic conditions on the stability of the landslide.
4. Soil deformation characteristics: The influence of soil deformation characteristics on landslide stability will be considered in the model, including soil compression characteristics, shear deformation and other factors. Through reasonable parameter selection and estimation, the stability of soil under different deformation states can be evaluated.
5. Parameter selection and fitting: When using the Fellenius model, you need to select the appropriate parameters, fit and adjust. The choice of parameters often relies on site survey data, laboratory test results, or other engineering experience.""" .


