                                                                                            rdfs:comment "" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Flexure_test
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Flexure_test> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus> ;
                                                                                      <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Flexural Test: Flexural test is used to determine the flexural strength and modulus of elasticity of materials such as rock and concrete. In a flexure test, a numerical value of the modulus of elasticity can be calculated by applying a moment load and recording the deformation and stress of the material.。" ;
                                                                                      rdfs:comment "" .


