                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Groundwater is an important factor for slope stability, and water is an important factor for landslide induction. The underwater permeable slope will be subjected to buoyancy force, the surface of impervious slope will be subjected to hydrostatic pressure, the flushing open crack will be subjected to the hydrostatic pressure of fracture water, and the groundwater seepage will produce hydrodynamic pressure on the slope. Water also has a softening effect on the rock and soil mass in the slope slip zone, which reduces the shear strength of the rock and soil mass【Engineering Geology,Lu Zhaozhen】" .


