###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hadning-Soyle_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hadning-Soyle_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> ,
                                                                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                               owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                               owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                             ] ,
                                                                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                               owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                               owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                             ] ,
                                                                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                               owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                               owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                             ] ,
                                                                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                               owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                               owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                             ] ,
                                                                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                               owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                               owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                             ] ;
                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Hardened soil model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                              "The Hardening-Soil model is a constitutive model for considering soil strength and deformation hardening, and is widely used for the analysis of slope stability and foundation foundations." ;
                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Elastoplastic behavior: The Hardening-Soil model treats soil as an elastoplastic material, taking into account both the elastic and plastic behavior of the soil. In the model, the elastic behavior of the soil is carried by nodes on the background mesh, while the plastic behavior is simulated by an offloading and reloading algorithm.
2. Constitutive Relations: The Hardening-Soil model uses a set of constitutive equations to describe the stress-strain relationship of soils. These constitutive equations typically include elastic constitutive equations and plastic constitutive equations. The elastic constitutive equation is used to describe the behavior of the soil during the elastic phase, while the plastic constitutive equation is used to describe the behavior of the soil during the plastic phase.
3. Strength Increase and Damage: The Hardening-Soil model takes into account the strength increase and damage process of the soil. In the model, the strength of the soil increases with the increase of plastic deformation, which reflects the hardening behavior of the soil. At the same time, the model also considers the damage process of the soil, that is, when the stress exceeds a certain threshold, the soil may crack and shear zone formation.
4. Model Parameters: The parameters of the Hardening-Soil model include elastic modulus, shear modulus, background mesh parameters, etc. These parameters need to be determined by laboratory tests or field observations in order for the model to accurately describe the mechanical properties of the soil.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Head_method
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Head_method> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                     rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability> ,
                                                                                                     <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient> ;
                                                                                     <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Head method: By measuring the seepage rate of a fluid under different head heights on a rock sample, the permeability coefficient can be calculated using Darcy's law and the permeability flow theory." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                     "Head method: The water seepage rate in the pores is measured by setting water heads at different heights on rock samples, and the permeability is calculated by applying theoretical formulas such as Darcy's law." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/High-speed_landslides
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/High-speed_landslides> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Type_of_speed> ;
                                                                                               <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The disaster was so destructive that it was impossible to evacuate all personnel due to its speed, resulting in some casualties" .


