###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hoek-Brown_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hoek-Brown_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                          rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> ;
                                                                                          <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Hawke-Brown model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                           "The Hoek-Brown model is a constitutive model used in the field of rock engineering, which considers the integrity, deformation characteristics and failure criteria of rocks to describe the stability and failure characteristics of rock landslides." ;
                                                                                          <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Strength criterion: The Hoek-Brown model uses a strength criterion based on the internal stress state of the rock and the material properties of the rock. In this model, the failure of the rock is described as a criterion based on the strength parameters of the rock and the stress state, that is, when the equivalent stress of the rock reaches a certain strength criterion, the rock begins to fail.
2. Rock Properties: The Hoek-Brown model takes into account some important characteristics of rocks, including the cohesion and friction angle of the rock, as well as some parameters related to the rock structure and fracture surface. These parameters can be determined experimentally or empirically.
3. Stress-Strain Relationship: Once the rock reaches the failure criterion, the Hoek-Brown model determines the magnitude of the plastic strain of the rock based on the strength conditions and strain state of the rock. In the model, the influence of normal stress and shear stress on the deformation of the rock is considered, and the stress-strain relationship is established on this basis.
4. Model parameters: The key parameters of the Hoek-Brown model include cohesion, friction angle, and some parameters related to the rock structure, such as the strength characteristics of the rock structure plane. These parameters are usually determined by experiments, field observations, or other means.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Homogeneous_landslides
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Homogeneous_landslides> rdf:type owl:Class ;
