                                                                                                <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The homogeneous one has no obvious bedding, and the smooth surface is cylindrical or quadratic" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hydrodynamic_pressure
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hydrodynamic_pressure> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hydrological_force> ;
                                                                                               <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> """The main characteristics of hydrodynamic pressure include:
Erosion: Groundwater flow can cause erosion and erosion on the soil or rock surface, and long-term effects may lead to soil damage and stability problems.
Pore water pressure: The flow of groundwater leads to changes in the pore water pressure inside the soil or rock, which directly affects the strength and deformation characteristics of the soil or rock.
Changes in groundwater level: The flow of groundwater will cause changes in groundwater level, which will indirectly affect the stress state of soil or rock, and then affect the stability of the project.""" ,
                                                                                                                                                                                "The pressure exerted by the flow of groundwater on the soil or rock" .


