###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hydrostatic_pressure
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hydrostatic_pressure> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                              rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hydrological_force> ;
                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> """The main characteristics of hydrostatic pressure include:
Influence of groundwater level: The level of groundwater level directly affects the magnitude of hydrostatic pressure, so the change of groundwater level will cause the change of hydrostatic pressure.
Supporting effect: Hydrostatic pressure can provide a certain degree of support, especially in excavation, foundation engineering, etc., and has a certain impact on the stability of soil or rock.
Seepage pressure: Hydrostatic pressure also includes pressure due to groundwater seepage, which is caused by the seepage of pore water in soil or rock.""" ,
                                                                                                                                                                               "The pressure exerted on soil or rocks by still groundwater" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hyperbolic_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hyperbolic_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                          rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> ,
                                                                                                          [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                            owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                            owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                          ] ,
                                                                                                          [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                            owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                            owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                          ] ,
                                                                                                          [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                            owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                            owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                          ] ;
                                                                                          <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Hyperbolic model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                           "The Hyperbolic model is a constitutive model used to describe the nonlinear behavior of soil, which is suitable for considering the elastoplastic and creep behavior of soil at high stress levels." ;
                                                                                          <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """This model is used to describe the stress-strain relationship of soils and is particularly suitable for the behavior analysis of elastoplastic materials. The hyperbolic model takes into account the nonlinear elastic and plastic behavior of the soil, as well as the stress relaxation effect of the soil during loading and unloading.

The hyperbolic model is based on the elastoplastic theory, and when the stress state reaches a certain level, the soil enters the plastic deformation stage. The model uses a hyperbola to describe the stress-strain relationship of the soil, which includes an elastic part and a plastic part. By defining criteria and flow rules, hyperbolic models can predict parameters such as failure criteria, plastic regions, and stress-strain curves of the soil.""" .


