###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Janbu_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Janbu_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                     rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Empirical_model> ,
                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength>
                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                     ] ;
                                                                                     <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The Janbu model is another empirical model for slope stability analysis, which takes into account the strength and shear deformation characteristics of the soil and provides stability analysis results based on the stress state of the soil." ,
                                                                                                                                                                      "Yanbu model" ;
                                                                                     <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Force Equilibrium Principle: The Janbu model is also based on the Force Balancing Principle, which considers the force of the landslide body in a stable state. In the model, the balance analysis of various forces on the landslide body, including self-weight, support force, shear strength and the influence of hydraulic factors on the landslide.
2. Soil shear strength: The shear strength characteristics of soil materials will be considered in the model, and the shear strength of the landslide body under different conditions will be evaluated by determining the shear strength parameters of the soil.
3. Hydraulic factors: The Janbu model also takes into account the influence of hydraulic factors on the stability of the landslide, including seasonal changes caused by rainfall, changes in groundwater level, and other factors. The shear strength of the soil is modified according to the hydraulic conditions in the model to consider the influence of hydraulic conditions on the stability of the landslide.
4. Soil deformation characteristics: The influence of soil deformation characteristics on landslide stability will also be considered in the model, including soil compression characteristics, shear deformation and other factors. Through reasonable parameter selection and estimation, the stability of soil under different deformation states can be evaluated.
5. Parameter selection and fitting: It is also necessary to reasonably select and fit the relevant parameters, and it is usually necessary to determine the values of these parameters based on field survey data, laboratory test results or other engineering experience.""" .


