                                                                                           <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Liquid Limit Test: The Liquid Limit Test is a commonly used soil cohesion test method, which is mainly applicable to cohesive soils. In the liquid limit test, the deformation characteristics of the soil under different water contents are observed by gradually adding water and stirring the soil sample, so as to determine the liquid limit and plasticity index. By calculating the plasticity index, an approximation of the cohesion of the soil can be obtained." .


