###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Modified_Cam-clay_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Modified_Cam-clay_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                 rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> ,
                                                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_modulus>
                                                                                                                 ] ,
                                                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                                 ] ,
                                                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                                 ] ,
                                                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                                 ] ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Improved - Cam-Clay model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                                  "The improvement of the traditional Cam-clay model can better simulate the nonlinear behavior of the soil during compression by introducing additional parameters" ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Plastic Potential Function: The modified Cam-Clay model uses a specific plastic potential function to describe the plastic behavior of the soil. This plastic potential function usually includes some parameters about the stress state of the soil, such as effective stress, void ratio, etc., which is used to describe the deformation characteristics of the soil under different stress states.
2. Stress-Strain Relationship: The modified Cam-Clay model establishes the relationship between stress and strain, considering the mechanical response of the soil during loading and unloading. The model usually includes parameters such as the compression index and expansion index of the soil to describe the deformation characteristics of the soil under different stress states.
3. Model parameters: The parameters of the modified Cam-Clay model are similar to those of the classical Cam-Clay model, including the initial compression index, initial expansion index, compression modulus, etc. of the soil. These parameters are usually determined by laboratory tests or site surveys.
4. Pore Water Pressure Effect: Like the classical Cam-Clay model, the modified Cam-Clay model also takes into account the influence of pore water pressure on soil strength and deformation characteristics. This enables the model to better describe the mechanical response of saturated and unsaturated soils.""" .


