###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Nonlinear_elastoplastic_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Nonlinear_elastoplastic_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                       rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> ,
                                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength>
                                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                                       ] ;
                                                                                                       <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "For some specific geotechnical materials, it may be necessary to use more complex constitutive models in landslide slope simulation, such as considering the nonlinear elastoplastic behavior of the material, to more accurately describe the slope's behavior during stress." ;
                                                                                                       <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Elastic behavior: In the range of small strains, the soil exhibits linear elastic behavior, i.e., the strain is proportional to the stress. This can be described by Hooke's law, where the relationship between the stress tensor and the strain tensor is linear. In landslide mechanics, a linear elastic model is often used to describe the behavior of a soil in a small strain range.
2. Plastic behavior: Plastic deformation occurs when a soil body is subjected to stresses that exceed its elastic limit. Plastic deformation is non-reversible, and even if the stress is reduced, the soil will still maintain plastic deformation. Plastic behavior is often described using flow rules (flow criteria), where the evolution of the stress tensor is related to the evolution of the strain tensor.
3. Failure behavior: Failure occurs when a soil body is subjected to stresses that exceed its strength limit. Failure is often described by a failure criterion, which defines the failure conditions and failure modes of the soil.
4. Nonlinear behavior: The nonlinear elastoplastic model takes into account the nonlinear behavior of the soil, that is, the stress-strain relationship of the soil is nonlinear during loading and unloading. This requires appropriate constitutive relations to describe the nonlinear response of soils, such as the Mohr-Coulomb model, the Drucker-Prager model and the Cam-Clay model.""" .


