###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Numerical_simulation_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Numerical_simulation_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                    rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/d._Mechanical_model> ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Rainfall_parameters>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Vegetation_parameters>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Slope,_aspect,_elevation>
                                                                                                                    ] ;
                                                                                                    <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> """Geological parameters: Geological parameters are one of the most important parameters in the process of simulating landslides. They describe the mechanical and hydrological properties of a soil or rock, including the elastic modulus of the soil, shear strength, pore water pressure, etc. These parameters can be obtained through field surveys, geological surveys, and laboratory tests.

Topographic parameters: Topographic parameters describe the topographic characteristics of the area where the landslide occurs, such as slope, aspect, elevation, etc. These parameters can be obtained through topographic surveys and digital elevation models (DEMs).

Rainfall parameters: Rainfall is one of the main factors that trigger landslides. Rainfall parameters include rainfall intensity, rainfall duration, and frequency, among others. These parameters can be obtained from meteorological records and rainfall observation data.

Vegetation parameters: Vegetation has an important impact on the stability of landslides. Vegetation parameters include root shear strength, root distribution, etc. These parameters can be obtained through vegetation surveys and field observations.

Boundary Condition Parameters: Boundary condition parameters define the boundary state of the simulation area, such as initial stress state, water level, and so on. These parameters can be obtained from field measurements and monitoring data.

Material parameters: Material parameters describe the properties of the materials used in the simulation, such as soil type, particle size, density, and so on. These parameters can be obtained through laboratory experiments and field sampling.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Osmosis_experiments
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Osmosis_experiments> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability> ,
                                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient> ,
                                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure> ;
                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Penetration test: A permeation test is applied to an osmosis instrument to observe the permeability rate of a fluid in a rock sample. According to Darcy's law and the theory of permeable flow, the permeability coefficient can be calculated." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                             "Permeability experiment: By applying external pressure and observing the permeability behavior of water in the pores, the permeability and osmotic pressure of the pore water can be obtained, so as to obtain the relevant information of the pore water pressure." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                             "Permeability test: The permeability rate of water in the rock sample is calculated by applying a certain pressure using the permeation instrument." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                      rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/c._Physical_parameters> ;
                                                                                      <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "A physical quantity that describes the ability of a porous medium such as rock, soil, etc., to permeate a fluid, usually water. It measures the ability of a fluid to conduct in a porous medium, i.e., the amount of fluid passing through a porous medium per unit area per unit of time." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                  rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/c._Physical_parameters> ;
                                                                                                  <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The permeability coefficient usually refers to the permeability of the soil or rock to water, that is, the ability of water to travel through the soil or rock力" .


