                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                        ] ,
                                                                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                          owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                          owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Slope,_aspect,_elevation>
                                                                                                        ] ;
                                                                                        <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> """Soil or rock mechanical parameters: including elastic modulus, Poisson's ratio, shear strength, etc. These parameters can be obtained from indoor trials, outdoor trials, or data from existing literature and databases.

Pore water parameters: including saturation, permeability coefficient, pore water pressure, etc. These parameters can be obtained from hydrological observations, hydrological experiments, or data from existing literature and databases.

Friction parameters: including internal friction angle, friction coefficient, etc. These parameters can be obtained from indoor trials, outdoor trials, or data from existing literature and databases.

Seepage parameters: including permeability, permeability, etc. These parameters can be obtained from hydrological observations, hydrological experiments, or data from existing literature and databases.

Material Density Parameter: Describes the density properties of a soil or rock. These parameters can be obtained through field sampling, laboratory trials, or data from existing literature and databases.

Deformation Parameters: Describes the strain properties of a soil or rock, including compressive modulus, shear modulus, and so on. These parameters can be obtained from indoor trials, outdoor trials, or data from existing literature and databases.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Physical_model_stage
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Physical_model_stage> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                              rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Physical_model> ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Boundary_parameters>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cohesion>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Slope,_aspect,_elevation>
                                                                                                              ] ;
                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The physical model stage is a specially designed experimental device for simulating the mechanical behavior of geological structures and slopes. It can include various elements that simulate soil, water flow, and slope surfaces." ;
                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Similarity principle: The design of the physical model table is based on the similarity principle, that is, the actual landslide system is reduced to a model. This requires ensuring similarity in terms of geometric dimensions, stress states, material properties, etc. By reasonably selecting the size ratio of the model and the actual system, the stress field and deformation behavior in the model can be similar to the actual situation.
2. Material Simulation: In order to simulate the mechanical properties of soil, a common method is to use model soil on a physical model table instead of the actual soil. Model soil usually uses a material with similar physical properties to the actual soil, such as powdery material, sand, clay, etc. The parameters such as density, particle size distribution, cohesion and internal friction angle of the model soil need to be selected and adjusted according to the actual soil characteristics.
3. Loading Condition Simulation: On the physical model table, appropriate loading conditions need to be applied to simulate the mechanical action in the actual landslide environment. This may include dead weight, hydraulic pressure, seismic loads, etc. By applying appropriate loads and boundary conditions, it is possible to simulate the mechanical response in the actual landslide, such as the displacement, stress distribution and deformation morphology of the soil.
4. Measurement and observation: The physical model stage is equipped with sensors and measuring equipment to monitor the changes of various parameters during the experiment. These parameters include displacement, stress, strain, etc. By measuring and recording this data in real time, combined with actual observations on the model table, information about the landslide behavior and failure mechanism can be obtained.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Hydrological_force> ,
                                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/c._Physical_parameters> ;
                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Refers to the pressure generated by the moisture present in the rock or soil. When there is moisture in a rock layer or soil, the water fills the pore space of the rock layer or soil, forming pore water. Due to the effect of gravity and pore structure, pore water generates a certain pressure, which is called pore water pressure." ,
                                                                                                                                                                              """The magnitude of pore water pressure depends on several factors:
Head difference: The pore water pressure varies with the change of the head difference, and the larger the head difference, the greater the pore water pressure.
Pore structure: The shape, size, and distribution of pores affect the transfer and distribution of pore water pressure.
Changes in the volume of pore water: When the pore water is squeezed or subjected to external stress, the volume of pore water changes, which in turn causes a change in pore water pressure.
Seepage: The flow of pore water can also have an effect on pore water pressure, especially when groundwater flows or drainage.""" ,
                                                                                                                                                                              "When water is present in a soil or rock, the pressure exerted by water molecules on the pore walls is known as pore water pressure. Affects the strength and deformation characteristics of soil or rock" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Prastić-Big_Marco_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Prastić-Big_Marco_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                 rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Constitutive_model> ,
                                                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                                 ] ,
                                                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                                 ] ,
                                                                                                                 [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                   owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                   owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                                 ] ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "A constitutive model that combines plastic deformation and damage evolution is suitable for describing the elastoplastic and damage behavior of soils. It is very useful for simulating cracks and damage to soil during loading" ,
                                                                                                                                                                                  "Plastic damage model" ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Plastic behavior: The Plastic-Damage model treats the soil as a plastic material with plastic deformation capabilities. In the model, the plastic behavior of the soil is controlled by the plastic strain rate, and the plastic strain is determined according to the yield criterion of the material. Commonly used plasticity criteria include Mohr-Coulomb criterion, Drucker-Prager criterion, etc.
2. Damage behavior: The Plastic-Damage model considers the damage behavior of the soil, i.e., the microcrack propagation and failure that may occur during the loading process. Damage is usually expressed in terms of damage variables, which range from 0 (no damage) to 1 (complete destruction). The evolutionary equation of the damage variable can be determined based on experimental data or empirical formulas.
3. Constitutive Relations: The Plastic-Damage model uses a set of constitutive equations to describe the stress-strain relationship of soils. These constitutive equations typically include plastic constitutive equations and damage constitutive equations. The plastic constitutive equation is used to describe the plastic behavior of the soil, while the damage constitutive equation is used to describe the damage behavior of the soil. By combining these two constitutive equations, the plastic deformation and damage evolution of soil during the landslide process can be simulated.
4. Model parameters: The parameters of the Plastic-Damage model include plastic parameters, damage parameters, etc. These parameters need to be determined by laboratory tests or field observations to enable the model to accurately describe the mechanical properties and damage behavior of the soil.。""" .


