                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Boundary_parameters>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cohesion>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                           ] ,
                                                                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                             owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                             owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Slope,_aspect,_elevation>
                                                                                                           ] ;
                                                                                           <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Use large soil grooves to simulate the physical model of an actual daylight or slope. These models can be carried out in a laboratory setting to observe the movement of the soil and the occurrence of landslides by tilting the soil groove." ;
                                                                                           <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """Principle of geometric similarity: The soil groove model has a certain proportional relationship with the actual landslide area in terms of size to maintain geometric similarity. Size scaling is usually determined based on principles such as Froude similarity or Reynolds similarity.

Material similarity principle: The soil material used in the soil groove model should have similar physical and mechanical properties to the soil material in the actual landslide area. The soil materials commonly used can be clay, sand, simulated soil, etc.

Setting of boundary conditions: The groove model needs to set up appropriate boundary conditions to simulate the actual landslide conditions. Boundary conditions can include the slope and aspect of the slope, the initial state of the soil, hydrological conditions, water table, and so on.

Simulating loading: In the groove model, external forces in actual landslide events are simulated by applying appropriate loading. The loading method can be gravity loading, hydraulic loading, vibration loading, etc.

Observation and measurement: In the process of soil groove model experiment, the changes of soil displacement, deformation, stress and other parameters are monitored and recorded in real time by installing sensors and measuring equipment. Commonly used observation methods include displacement gauges, strain gauges, manometers, inclinometers, etc.""" .


