###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Spencer_model
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Spencer_model> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                       rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Empirical_model> ,
                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength>
                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Pore_water_pressure>
                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                       ] ,
                                                                                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                         owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                         owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                       ] ;
                                                                                       <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "Spencer model" ,
                                                                                                                                                                        "The Spencer model is one of the empirical models used for slope stability analysis. The model takes into account the shape of the slope, the properties of the soil, and the load conditions on the slope surface, and evaluates the stability of the slope by considering these factors." ;
                                                                                       <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Force Balance Principle: The Spencer model is also based on the force balance principle, considering the force of the landslide body in a steady state. In the model, the balance analysis of various forces on the landslide body, including self-weight, support force, shear strength and the influence of hydraulic factors on the landslide.
2. Soil strength parameters: The internal friction angle and shear strength of the soil material are considered in the model, which reflect the shear resistance of the soil. Through reasonable parameter selection and estimation, the stability of soil under different conditions can be evaluated.
3. Hydrological factors: The Spencer model will also consider the influence of hydrological factors on the stability of landslides, including seasonal changes caused by rainfall, groundwater level changes and other factors, which will have an important impact on the stability of the soil.
4. Topographic factors: The influence of topographic factors on the stability of landslides is usually considered in the model, such as slope, landform and other factors will be taken into account in the model.
5. Parameter selection and fitting: It is also necessary to reasonably select and fit the relevant parameters, and it is usually necessary to determine the values of these parameters based on field survey data, laboratory test results or other engineering experience.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Static_compression_test
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Static_compression_test> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                 rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_modulus> ,
                                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength> ,
                                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio> ;
                                                                                                 <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Static compression test: In a static compression test, a rock sample is placed in a compression testing machine and a progressively increasing axial pressure is applied until the rock sample cracks. By measuring the maximum bearing capacity and deformation of the rock sample, the compressive strength of the rock can be calculated." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                                 "Static compression test: In a static compression test, a rock sample is placed in a special compression testing machine, a progressively increasing axial pressure is applied, and the corresponding axial strain is measured. By plotting the stress-strain curve and performing a slope analysis, the compressive modulus of the rock can be obtained." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                                 "Static compression test: The Poisson's ratio of a rock can also be determined when performing a static compression test. In the test, the Poisson's ratio of the rock can also be calculated by applying axial pressure and measuring the lateral strain in the vertical direction." ;
                                                                                                 rdfs:comment "" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Static_tensile_test
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Static_tensile_test> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                             rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio> ;
                                                                                             <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Static tensile test: In a static tensile test, a rock sample is placed in a tensile testing machine and a progressively increasing axial tensile force is applied until the rock sample cracks. By measuring the fracture stress and fracture strain of the rock sample, the tensile strength of the rock can be calculated." ,
                                                                                                                                                                                             "Static tensile test: In a static tensile test, a rock sample is placed in a tensile testing machine, a progressively increasing axial tensile force is applied, and the transverse strain of the rock sample is measured at the same time. From the calculated stress-strain relationship, the Poisson's ratio of the rock can be obtained." .


