###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Tilt_shear_test
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Tilt_shear_test> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                         rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength> ;
                                                                                         <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Oblique shear test: The oblique shear test is a commonly used experimental method that simulates the stress state in real engineering by applying a shear force on a rock sample while applying a forward pressure perpendicular to the shear plane through inclined loading. By measuring parameters such as shear strength and friction angle of rock samples, the shear strength of the rock can be calculated." .


