###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Triaxial_test_of_rocks
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Triaxial_test_of_rocks> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength> ;
                                                                                                <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> "Rock triaxial test: Rock triaxial test is a commonly used experimental method that can apply axial pressure and stress in two perpendicular directions at the same time, so that the rock sample is stressed in three directions, which eventually leads to the fracture of the rock sample. By measuring the stress-strain relationship of rock samples, the compressive strength of the rock can be obtained." ;
                                                                                                rdfs:comment "" .


