###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Finite_Difference_Method_(FDM)）
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Finite_Difference_Method_(FDM)）> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                         rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Numerical_simulation_model> ,
                                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability>
                                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                                         ] ,
                                                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                                         ] ;
                                                                                                         <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The finite difference method discretizes the solution domain into a grid, and transforms the continuous problem into a discrete problem by approximating the derivative term in the differential equation. In landslide research, the finite difference method is often used to simulate physical processes such as deformation, seepage and heat conduction of landslide bodies." ;
                                                                                                         <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Discretization: First, the landslide area is divided into small units or grids to facilitate the discretization of continuous problems. In the finite difference method, grids are often used to represent discrete points in space, while temporal is handled by discretization of time steps.
2. Equation establishment: At each discrete point, an equation describing the mechanical behavior of the landslide, such as the momentum balance equation, the equation of motion, etc., is established. These equations can be used to select the appropriate material model and boundary conditions according to the actual situation.
3. Differential approximation: Replace the derivative term in a differential equation with a finite difference approximation, such as using the central difference, forward difference, or backward difference to approximate the differential term, thereby transforming the differential equation into a difference equation.
4. Time integration: The finite difference method usually uses explicit or implicit time integration methods to simulate the evolution process in time. In the explicit method, the solution of the next time step can be calculated directly from the solution of the current time step, while in the implicit method, the solution of the next time step is obtained by solving a system of equations.
5. Boundary conditions: In the simulation, the boundary conditions applied to the boundary of the landslide body need to be considered, and these conditions can include externally applied forces, displacement boundary conditions, etc.
6. Solving equations: By solving the discretized difference equations, you can obtain displacement, velocity, stress and other information on each discrete point.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Finite_Element_Method_(FEM)
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Finite_Element_Method_(FEM)> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                     rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Numerical_simulation_model> ,
                                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                                     ] ,
                                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                       owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                       owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                                     ] ;
                                                                                                     <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The finite element method discretizes a complex structure or geological body into finite elements and establishes a mesh consisting of nodes and elements. By establishing the appropriate interpolation function and strength criterion on each element, the mechanical equation is solved by numerical calculation method, so as to simulate the deformation and stability of the landslide body." ;
                                                                                                     <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Discretization: For the area of the landslide to be studied, it is discretized into many small finite element elements. Each finite element element can be a point, line, or area element, and the combination of these small elements approximates the mechanical properties of the entire landslide area.
2. Establish equations: Establish corresponding mechanical equations according to the theory of elastic mechanics and the mechanical properties of the material itself. The equilibrium equation and the constitutive relationship of materials are usually used to describe the force and deformation of the landslide body.
3. Boundary Conditions: Determine the boundary conditions of the landslide model, including the force boundary and the displacement boundary conditions. These boundary conditions reflect the interaction between the landslide body and the external environment or support structure.
4. Numerical solution: The established mechanical equation is solved by numerical methods, and the original differential equation can be discretized into a system of equations by the finite element method, and then the approximate solution of the system of equations is obtained by numerical solution methods (such as iterative method).
5. Result analysis: According to the results of numerical simulation, the mechanical parameters such as stress, strain, and displacement of the landslide body under different conditions can be obtained, and then the stability, deformation characteristics and possible failure modes of the landslide body can be analyzed.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Finite_Volume_Method_(FVM)
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Finite_Volume_Method_(FVM)> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                    rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Numerical_simulation_model> ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                                    ] ,
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                                    ] ;
                                                                                                    <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The finite volume method divides the solution domain into discrete control volumes, and solves for changes in the physics by integrating the conservation equations for mass, momentum, and energy in each control volume. In landslide research, the finite volume method is often used to simulate the seepage and mass transport processes of landslide bodies." ;
                                                                                                    <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Meshing: First, the landslide area needs to be meshed to decompose the entire problem domain into many small control volumes, each of which contains one or more discrete points.
2. Conservation equations: For the physical equations of the conserved form (such as conservation of mass, conservation of momentum, conservation of energy, etc.), they are integrated in each control volume to obtain the discretized conservation equation.
3. Flux calculation: In the finite volume method, the flux needs to be calculated on the boundary of each control volume, and the flux represents the transfer of physical quantities between adjacent control volumes, which is usually calculated by the method of flux interpolation.
4. Numerical solving: By solving the discretized conservation equation, the evolution of physical quantities (such as density, velocity, pressure, etc.) on each control volume over time can be obtained.""" .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Fusion_Discrete_and_Continuous_Methods_(CDCM)）
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Fusion_Discrete_and_Continuous_Methods_(CDCM)）> rdf:type owl:Class ;
