                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Elastic_modulus>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Permeability_coefficient>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_modulus>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Poisson's_ratio>
                                                                                                                              ] ;
                                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The hybrid finite element method is used to solve both displacement and stress fields and is suitable for problems involving the interaction of incompressible fluids and solids." ;
                                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Variable selection: The traditional finite element method usually only uses displacement as the main variable to describe the deformation behavior of a structure or soil, but in landslide mechanics, using displacement as the only variable may lead to a large calculation error. Therefore, the hybrid finite element method introduces two variables, displacement and stress, to more accurately describe the mechanical behavior of the landslide body.
2. Discretization: Similar to the traditional finite element method, the hybrid finite element method discretizes the landslide body into a finite number of elements, and describes the physical behavior within each element through the displacements and stresses on the nodes. The difference is that the hybrid finite element method uses different types of elements, such as displacement elements and stress elements, to describe the distribution of displacements and stresses, respectively.
3. Variational Principle: The hybrid finite element method is based on the variational principle, which derives a discretized system of equations by minimizing the energy functional. The Lagrangian multiplier method is used to connect the two variables of displacement and stress to establish a coupled system of equations.
4. Basis Functions and Interpolation: In the hybrid finite element method, the distribution of displacements and stresses is usually interpolated using different types of basis functions. Displacement variables typically use highly continuous basis functions, such as linear or quadratic basis functions, while stress variables use discontinuous basis functions, such as constant or linear basis functions. By selecting the appropriate basis function, the real behavior of the landslide body can be better approximated.
5. Numerical solving: The hybrid finite element method uses numerical methods to solve discretized equations. Common solution methods include iterative method, matrix inversion method, etc. By iteratively calculating the displacement and stress within each element, the deformation and mechanical response of the landslide body can be obtained.""" .


