###  http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Rigid_Body_Limit_Equilibrium_(RLEM)）
<http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Rigid_Body_Limit_Equilibrium_(RLEM)）> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                              rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Numerical_simulation_model> ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Boundary_parameters>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Cohesion>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Compressive_strength>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Internal_friction_angle>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Material_parameters>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Shear_strength>
                                                                                                                              ] ,
                                                                                                                              [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                owl:onProperty <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/requiredParameters> ;
                                                                                                                                owl:someValuesFrom <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/Slope,_aspect,_elevation>
                                                                                                                              ] ;
                                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/comment> "The rigid body limit equilibrium method is an analytical method based on rigid body mechanics and equilibrium conditions. It assumes that the landslide body is a rigid body, and estimates the stability and possible sliding surface of the landslide body by equilibrium equations. This approach is often suitable for studying smaller-scale landslides or simplified stability problems." ;
                                                                                                              <http://www.semanticweb.org/94180/ontologies/2023/3/untitled-ontology-8/principle_of_the_model> """1. Rigid body assumption: The rigid body limit equilibrium method assumes that the landslide body is a rigid body, that is, it ignores the deformation and displacement inside the landslide body and simplifies it into a system composed of multiple rigid bodies. This assumption makes the analysis and calculation relatively simple and suitable for a preliminary assessment of the overall stability.
2. Equilibrium Condition: According to the principle of static equilibrium, for each rigid body, the rigid body limit equilibrium method takes into account the equilibrium relationship between gravity, support force and sliding resistance. In the equilibrium state, the force condition of the landslide body should meet the conditions of moment balance and force balance.
3. Friction angle and shear strength: In order to perform stability analysis, parameters such as internal friction angle and shear strength of the landslide material need to be determined. These parameters can be obtained by means of field investigation and laboratory tests, and are used to calculate the sliding surface inside the landslide body and the shear stress on it.
4. Possible Sliding Surface Search: In the rigid body limit equilibrium method, it is necessary to search and evaluate possible sliding surfaces. Generally speaking, the sliding surface is usually along the weak zone or existing crack surface inside the rock and soil mass, and the rigid body limit equilibrium method evaluates the stability of the landslide body by searching for possible sliding surfaces.
5. Stability criterion: The relationship between shear stress and shear strength on each possible sliding surface is calculated by using the rigid body limit equilibrium method, so as to determine the stability of the landslide body. When the calculated safety factor is less than 1, it means that the landslide is in danger of instability.""" .


